{"id":"decision-example-001","type":"decision","fact":"Example: Chose Zustand over Redux for client state management because of simpler API and smaller bundle size.","recommendation":"Use Zustand stores for client state. Use TanStack Query for server state. Do not mix the two patterns.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"human","reference":"Architecture decision","date":"2026-01-09"}],"tags":["architecture","state-management","zustand"],"affectedFiles":["src/stores/**/*.ts"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-01-09T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-01-09T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"decision-trending-cursor-stability","type":"decision","fact":"Trending sort cursor pagination uses created_at as the stable keyset key instead of the computed time-decay score, because the score shifts every second and would produce incorrect pagination.","recommendation":"For trending feed pagination, ORDER BY the computed score but use created_at+id for the WHERE clause in cursor-based keyset pagination. Accept slight ordering drift between pages.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #17 design spec — security review + spec review","date":"2026-04-12"}],"tags":["pagination","cursor","trending","feed","postgresql"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/src/db/queries/feed.ts"],"affectedServices":["findFeedPosts"],"createdAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"decision-ws-sender-exclusion-header","type":"decision","fact":"WebSocket sender exclusion for REST-triggered broadcasts uses an `x-ws-client-id` request header, NOT attachment of a socket reference to the Fastify request during auth. REST and WebSocket connections are separate TCP connections, so the auth plugin cannot know which WebSocket belongs to the HTTP caller without a client-sent correlator.","recommendation":"On WebSocket auth-ok, generate a UUID clientId and register it in ConnectionManager. Client composable exposes clientId and apiFetch injects `x-ws-client-id` on POST/PATCH/PUT/DELETE. Server routes read the header, look up the socket via `connections.findByClientId(id)`, and pass as `excludeWs` to `channels.broadcast`.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #1 plan review gate","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["websocket","real-time","broadcast","architecture"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/src/plugins/websocket/**/*.ts","packages/server/src/routes/**/*.ts","packages/client/src/lib/api.ts","packages/client/src/composables/useWebSocket.ts"],"affectedServices":["ChannelManager","ConnectionManager"],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"decision-ws-bruno-exemption","type":"decision","fact":"The /ws WebSocket endpoint is exempted from the CLAUDE.md Bruno gate because Bruno CLI is HTTP-only and cannot drive WebSocket frame-level interaction (no send of auth/subscribe frames, no assertions on server-sent frames). Plain HTTP against /ws returns 400 without revealing protocol correctness.","recommendation":"Document the exemption explicitly in the feature's plan under Design Decisions. Cover WebSocket correctness via unit tests on the handler state machine, client composable tests with a fake WebSocket, and manual two-tab verification during integration. REST routes touched by WS broadcast wiring still run the existing Bruno collection to catch regressions.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #1 plan review gate","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["bruno","websocket","testing","gate-exemption"],"affectedFiles":["bruno/**/*.bru","packages/server/src/plugins/websocket/**/*.ts"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"decision-tailwind-v4-primary-opacity-palette","type":"decision","fact":"The client uses Tailwind v4 with a single custom --color-primary CSS variable (defined via @theme in main.css) and NO numbered primary palette. Attempts to use bg-primary-50, bg-primary-900/40, text-primary-600, etc. produce undefined utility classes; the project consistently uses bg-primary, bg-primary/10, bg-primary/20, bg-primary/90 (base color + opacity modifier) everywhere a primary-tinted background is needed.","recommendation":"When a component or plan calls for a primary-tinted background at a specific lightness level, use the opacity-modifier form bg-primary/<n> instead of a numbered palette variant. For dark-mode pairs follow the established pattern bg-primary/10 dark:bg-primary/20 (see PostMetaHeader.vue, SearchResultItem.vue).","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #3 WU-9 adversarial review","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["tailwind","tailwind-v4","theming","color-palette","ui"],"affectedFiles":["packages/client/src/**/*.vue","packages/client/src/main.css"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"decision-ai-gate-shared-limiter-001","type":"decision","fact":"packages/server/src/plugins/langchain/index.ts constructs ONE AiRateLimiter instance and exposes it via app.aiGate = [app.authenticate, aiRateLimit]. All AI endpoints registered with { preHandler: app.aiGate } share the same limiter by construction — the 1-in-flight-per-user invariant is enforced at plugin-registration time, not per-route. Adding a new AI endpoint that uses app.aiGate automatically participates in the shared limit.","recommendation":"New AI endpoints MUST register with { preHandler: app.aiGate }. Do NOT build a custom preHandler chain that calls a fresh AiRateLimiter — that silently opts the endpoint out of the shared limit and lets a user hold two concurrent AI requests (autocomplete + generate, or two generates). If a future endpoint needs a different limit, extend the limiter inside langchain/index.ts rather than constructing a second instance.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"self-reflect","reference":"Issue #10 WU-004 satisfying DoD #5 by construction","date":"2026-04-14"}],"tags":["fastify","rate-limiting","ai","architecture","shared-state"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/src/plugins/langchain/index.ts","packages/server/src/routes/ai.ts"],"affectedServices":["AiRateLimiter","aiGate"],"createdAt":"2026-04-14T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-14T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
